The Order of Australia is the only Australian order of chivalry. It was
established on 14 February 1975 by Elizabeth II, Queen of Australia, to
recognise Australian citizens and other persons for achievement, meritorious
service, or for both. 'Companion of the Order of Australia' is the highest grade
of this Order currently awarded.

This is a list of 'Companions of the [[Order of Australia]]'.
